					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bisqwit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I traced the problem to be the following: At the beginning of the frame render, the nametable bitmask of T was set from Bits 0..1 of $2000. Apparently, it is only to be set when $2000 is written. The bits 0..1 of $2000 do not need to be stored anywhere permanently.</div>
<br />Like writes to PPUSCROLL ($2005), writes to PPUCTRL ($2000) bits 1 and 0 change only the value in <em>t</em> (background base address), which gets copied to <em>v</em> (background current address) near the end of line -1.</div>

